can you remove skin cancer very small area with salicylic acid a customer told me about her father in law who had been scheduled to have surgery for his skin cancer in two weeks he put tea tree oil on the lesion every day by the time of the scheduled surgery the lesion was completely gone and no surgery was required i've subsequently used tea tree oil on a suspicious irregular red spot on my face each time i do that the irregular red area goes away i've often not kept up with it and the red spot has returned several times each time i've attended to it for a few days it goes away again so wasn't a fluke that the tea tree oil worked the first time btw i've never met anyone who has had a skin cancer removed surgically who didn't subsequently have several more lesions appear that's because surgically removing the first one to appear activates the inactive sites good luck and be well kelley Acne Malignant melanoma Colorectal cancer Cancer Psoriasis Radiation therapy Wart Scar Cervical cancer Birthmark Breast cancer Renal cell carcinoma Circumcision Prostate cancer Endometrial cancer Basal cell carcinoma Skin graft Dermatology Esophageal cancer Androgen insensitivity syndrome Stomach cancer Keloid Tattoo Spina bifida Oral and maxillofacial surgery Sunscreen Intersex surgery Endocarditis Brain tumor DNA repair Skin cancer Urinary incontinence Endometriosis Wound healing phases Lung cancer Plastic surgery Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Sex reassignment surgery female-to-male Penis Saturday Night Live Kaposi's sarcoma Suture Herpes simplex virus Japanese tea ceremony Lance Armstrong Surgery Psychic surgery Lupus erythematosus Radiosurgery Abortion Neurofibromatosis type II Wilms' tumor Tuberculosis Tuberous sclerosis Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Heinkel He 100 Hysterectomy Adjustable gastric band Eczema Crohn's disease Reflex sympathetic dystrophy syndrome Kylie Minogue Human papillomavirus Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Epilepsy Insulin Puberty Mesothelioma Ovarian cancer Babe 